Leicester City legend Gary Lineker has praised a “stunning” Kelechi Iheanacho goal in Nigeria’s Group D opening win against Egypt at the Africa Cup of Nations(AFCON) Cameroon 2021. Striker Iheanacho scored the solitary winner in the 30th minute to give Nigeria the maximum three points of the match. The City star controlled the ball on the edge of the Egypt penalty box before he half-volleyed a shot into the top corner of the net. BBC presenter Lineker, a striker himself in his heyday, took to Twitter to praise the goal and declare his support for Nigeria throughout the tournament.   Sierra Leone holds Algeria in Group E opener     Salah brutally slammed on social media     Egypt’s Queiroz admits shoddy display   As well as Iheanacho, City are also represented in the Nigeria squad by midfielder Wilfred Ndidi, who also featured against Egypt. - Advertisement - “What a stunning goal from @67Kelechi,” Lineker tweeted.”Given the @LCFC connection, @NGSuperEagles are definitely my team in Africa Cup of Nations.” Meanwhile, City have two other players away at the tournament. Midfielder-turned-defender Daniel Amartey was in action for Ghana yesterday (Monday) as they suffered a 1-0 defeat to Morocco in their opening game. Papy Mendy, meanwhile, is in the Senegal squad but did not feature in their opener against Zimbabwe after testing positive for COVID-19.